		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=14219#comment-17140</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Such a great point, Scott, and one that I recently recognised in my learning journey with the bass. But the whole &#039;shiny object&#039; thing is something that can be found in so many things and areas of life, especially in these days of YouTube. It seems to me that that drive to &#039;know more stuff&#039; is very different to actually living what you know through applying it, and that difference can lead to a student (and let&#039;s face it, we&#039;re all students, just at different places in our journey) to thinking that they have mastery over something that they may know in their head but don&#039;t know how to actually use practically. 
Really great to get this exposed and out in the open! Thank you!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Such a great point, Scott, and one that I recently recognised in my learning journey with the bass. But the whole &#8216;shiny object&#8217; thing is something that can be found in so many things and areas of life, especially in these days of YouTube. It seems to me that that drive to &#8216;know more stuff&#8217; is very different to actually living what you know through applying it, and that difference can lead to a student (and let&#8217;s face it, we&#8217;re all students, just at different places in our journey) to thinking that they have mastery over something that they may know in their head but don&#8217;t know how to actually use practically.<br />
Really great to get this exposed and out in the open! Thank you!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
